The Starting Five
-----------------

* Chelsea=E2=80=99s Girma play: In January, Chelsea paid $1.1 million to po=
ach star player Naomi Girma from the NWSL, marking the first million-dollar=
 transfer in women=E2=80=99s soccer. On the Varsity podcast, I asked commis=
sioner Jessica Berman if this deal was a harbinger of things to come for th=
e growing league, which has a firm salary cap in place. =E2=80=9CIt is part=
 of the game. Players move between leagues,=E2=80=9D she said. =E2=80=9CTha=
t is known,
and understood, in men=E2=80=99s soccer, and for people in Europe. Secondly=
, as a general point, our players have value, and this is now an investable=
 business proposition. That=E2=80=99s great for women, and that=E2=80=99s g=
reat for women=E2=80=99s soccer. Third, we are structured very differently =
from the likes of the WSL [Women=E2=80=99s Super League], where Chelsea pla=
ys. =E2=80=A6 We live with a salary cap. We live in a world where we expect=
 our clubs to provide a consistent experience for players and fans, for tra=
ining facilities, for
stadiums. With all that in mind, we have to lean into the things that make =
us better, or great, and not try to be something that we=E2=80=99re not. On=
e of our superpowers is the competitiveness of our league.

She continued: =E2=80=9CDo I want Naomi here? 100 percent. I hope she comes=
 back. We will welcome her back with open arms. But when the hysteria start=
s, we have to level-set with some rationality about what is real and what i=
s not real in this world, and caution around getting too caught up in some
of those one-off situations that may not work in our favor. By the way, we =
brought in more players in this transfer window than we lost.=E2=80=9D
* Double bogie: PGA Tour commissioner Jay Monahan sat down with Golfweek=E2=
=80=99s Eamon Lynch for an in-depth interview that touched on everything fr=
om the PGA Tour=E2=80=99s LIV deal and Donald Trump=E2=80=99s involvement w=
ith the negotiations, to his own past mistakes when
